author: Min Zeng
title: U.S. Government Bonds Pull Back, Even With Tame Inflation Report
text:
U.S. Treasury bonds pulled back Wednesday despite a weaker-than-forecast inflation report.
Traders said the latest consumer prices index release won’t be a stumbling block for the Federal Reserve to start raising short-term interest rates as soon as next month.
